    {
      "content": "Your web app has over 10GB of content (that's the max amount you can backup at a time).",
      "pos": [
        6688,
        6775
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You don't want to back up the log files.",
      "pos": [
        6780,
        6820
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Partial backups will let you choose exactly which files you want to back up.",
      "pos": [
        6822,
        6898
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Exclude files from your backup",
      "pos": [
        6904,
        6934
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To exclude files and folders from your backups, create a <ph id=\"ph1\">`_backup.filter`</ph> file in the wwwroot folder of your web app and specify the list of files and folders you want to exclude in there.",
      "pos": [
        6936,
        7124
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An easy way to access this is through the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Kudu Console<ept id=\"p1\">](https://github.com/projectkudu/kudu/wiki/Kudu-console)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        7125,
        7237
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Suppose you have a web app that contains log files and static images from past years that are never going to change.",
      "pos": [
        7240,
        7356
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You already have a full backup of the web app that includes the old images.",
      "pos": [
        7357,
        7432
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Now you want to backup the web app every day, but you don't want to pay for storing log files or the static image files that never change.",
      "pos": [
        7433,
        7571
      ]
    },
