      "content": "![Logs Folder][LogsFolder]",
      "pos": [
        7573,
        7599
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "![Images Folder][ImagesFolder]",
      "pos": [
        7600,
        7630
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The below steps show how you would exclude these files from the backup.",
      "pos": [
        7636,
        7707
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Go to <ph id=\"ph1\">`http://{yourapp}.scm.azurewebsites.net/DebugConsole`</ph> and identify the folders that you want to exclude from your backups.",
      "pos": [
        7712,
        7840
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In this example, you would want to exclude the following files and folders shown in that UI:",
      "pos": [
        7841,
        7933
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8127,
        8224
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> The last line illustrates that you can exclude individuals files as well as folders."
    },
    {
      "content": "Create a file called <ph id=\"ph1\">`_backup.filter`</ph> and put the list above in the file, but remove <ph id=\"ph2\">`D:\\home`</ph>.",
