        9498,
        9643
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "How backups are stored",
      "pos": [
        9677,
        9699
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After you have made one or more backups for your web app, the backups will be visible on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Containers<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> blade of your storage account, as well as your web app.",
      "pos": [
        9701,
        9864
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In the storage account, each backup consists of a .zip file that contains the backup data and an .xml file that contains a manifest of the .zip file contents.",
      "pos": [
        9865,
        10023
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can unzip and browse these files if you want to access your backups without actually performing a web app restore.",
      "pos": [
        10024,
        10142
      ]
    },
    {
